# ============================================================
# FINANCE CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: finance
scope: finance.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for finance.

## policy_rules
Finance policy constrains:
- who may view which finance detail
- who may reserve, settle, approve, or dispute finance state
- what finance history may be disclosed
- when finance paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- control scope must be explicit
- settlement/approval scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded finance summary
- holder/operator detail
- reviewer/approver detail
- historical finance detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow finance action only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden widening of finance authority
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If finance context,
settlement basis,
approval scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the finance path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- finance-control policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
